---

<section class="relative h-[80vh] min-h-[560px] overflow-hidden">
  <img
    src="/assets/photos/sunset-chairs.jpg"
    alt="Guests in Adirondack chairs watching the sunset at Indian Rocks Beach"
    class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
  />
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-navy-deep/85 via-navy-deep/20 to-navy-deep/40"></div>

  <div class="relative h-full max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-10 flex flex-col justify-end pb-20 md:pb-24 text-sand-50 reveal">
    <div class="eyebrow text-sand-100/80 mb-5 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="inline-block w-6 h-px bg-sand-100/60"></span>
      And then, every evening
    </div>
    <p class="serif text-[34px] md:text-[56px] leading-[1.05] max-w-3xl">
      Two chairs, the Gulf, <span class="italic font-light">and a sky that does the rest.</span>
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6 text-[14.5px] md:text-[15.5px] text-sand-100/85 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
      Sunset here is a nightly ritual — take a chair down to the sand and stay until the last of the orange is gone.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
